	Donald Trump’s proposal to bar all Muslims from entering the United States violates U.S. and international law and would never be allowed by the courts, legal scholars said late Monday.

	“Oh, for the love of God,” said Jonathan Turley, a constitutional law expert at George Washington University. 


In response to this backlash, Trump started making fewer statements about a ban on Muslims and instead starting saying he planned to ban travel from certain territories:


